Two people died in a head-on collision on the R330 between Humansdorp and St Francis Bay in the Eastern Cape on Monday. Deputy Director of Eastern Cape Traffic Charles Bramwell said the crash occurred between a Kia SUV and Hyundai Etios on Monday afternoon. Bramwell said two women passed away and two other passengers travelling in the Etios were in a serious condition at hospital. A third vehicle a VolksWagen Amarok travelling behind the Etios at the time was also involved in the accident but passengers in the vehicle sustained no injuries. African News Agency (ANA)